@jomarko thanks for your review and your question.
ImmutableList should be better because it's really immutable. Collections.unmodifiableList is not immutable: rather, it's a view that receivers can't change, but the original source can change.
My opinion: Since we don't need to add new dependencies (because Guava is already available) I think we can exploit Guava's benefits
